                    [Raspberry Pi 4]
                        +--------------------------+
                        |                          |
                        |   USB-C Power Input      |
                        |                          |
                        |   GPIO17 ─────────┐      |
                        |   (Fan control)   │      |
                        |                  ┌▼┐     |
                        |   GPIO27 ─────┐  │ │     |
                        | (SSR control) │  │ │     |
                        |               ▼  ▼ ▼     |
                        +---------------┬--┬--+    |
                                        |  |       |
                                    [SunFounder 2-Channel Relay]
                                        |  |
              +-------------------------┘  └---------------------------+
              |                                                           |
     Channel 1 (IN1)                                              Channel 2 (IN2)
     │                                                            │
     ▼                                                            ▼
[Controls SSR DC +]                                     [Controls 120V AC Fan Line]
     │                                                            │
     │                                                            ▼
     │                                                [120V AC Cooling Fan]
     ▼
[Solid State Relay]
(DC side: 3–32V) ←───────────────+
(AC side: 24–480V)               |
                                 ▼
                            [240V Kiln Elements]
                          (AIM 1413, 14 amps @ 240V)

----------------------------------------
[POWER SETUP – AC SIDE]

240V Wall Power (Hot1 + Hot2) ───►
    ├── Inline Fuse ───► SSR Input Terminal 1
    └──────────────────► Kiln Neutral (or Hot2 depending on split-phase wiring)
SSR Output Terminal 2 ───► Kiln Element Power Input

Fan Neutral ─────────────► AC Neutral Bus Bar
Grounds ────────────────► Proper Earth Ground

----------------------------------------
[SENSOR SETUP – MAX31855 K-Type Thermocouple Reader]

Thermocouple ──────► MAX31855
MAX31855 to Pi SPI Pins:
    VCC  ──────────► Pi 3.3V (or 5V if board allows)
    GND  ──────────► Pi GND
    DO   ──────────► Pi GPIO9 (MISO)
    CS   ──────────► Pi GPIO8 (CE0)
    CLK  ──────────► Pi GPIO11 (SCLK)

----------------------------------------

NOTES:
• Raspberry Pi powers the relay board through its 5V GPIO and GND pins.
• Each relay only requires 15–20mA, well within Pi’s limits.
• The SSR switches 240V to kiln ONLY via relay isolation.
• The fan can optionally be turned on/off based on Pi’s CPU temp.
• Inline fuse (or breaker) protects from overload.
• NEVER connect Pi GPIO directly to SSR or high voltage!
